
Generic NPC rules
-----------------

	o  No maintenance costs charged
	o  Do not automatically receive NP's
	o  NPCs are never taken prisoners; fight is always to the death
	o  May not use the STUDY order


Undead
------

	o  50% chance each dead enemy man becomes one of the undead.
		- undead don't take booty, prisoners?
			take_unit_item, take_prisoners
		- only booty undead take are men, they get changed
		  into undead?

	o  Health is always "dead" -- one hit kills an undead noble. (?)

	o  May summon a GHOST SHIP; cost 2NP.

		-  undead ship "Name of ship"

		-  ghost ship dissolves when no longer captained by
		   an undead noble

		-  Undead ghost ship captains do not need Sailing

	o  Undead PILLAGE causes hit to tax base, generates undead
	   followers instead of gold (1 undead to 10 gold).

	o  Undead gain 1 NP from victory in battle

	o  Undead never have less than 10 (units + NP's)

	o  Undead get a report for any graveyard with people nearby

	o  Undead may create a noble in any unoccupied graveyard

		undead form <where>

	o  undead dissolve

		undead units can reclaim themselves -- adds an NP

Undead items fight at=2, df=2:  "Undead move slowly and are not
very good fighters, but their gruesome appearance often strikes terror
into untrained fighters.  Seeing one's friends and relatives as enemies
on the battlefield, decomposing, is often unnerving."

