Okay, an undead army... lets see...


-If they won a combat, they'd get all the defeated troops in the form of
 undead whatever they were. (ie: if they killed a knight, they would get
 an undead knight.) They wouldn't get any troops that they lost and they
 would only get enemy troops if they won.

-No maintanance cost.

-If the pillage a city, they get troops instead of gold, but the tax base
 still goes down.

-They have one castle somewhere where only their nobles can learn skills
 and new nobles can be created. They can create a noble for free, but
 can only have 10 active nobles at a time.  An undead noble can only learn
 up to two skill categories (ie: Combat and Shipcraft)... no scratch that.
 When undead nobles are created, they auto know combat...

Umm... I gotta go eat dinner.

I'll think about it some more and get back to you



